      • addQuestion

        public com.solvvy.db.SolvvyTables.InsertionResult addQuestion(Question question,
                                                              int unfilteredSnippets)
        Adds a question if it's new; otherwise updates the number of times it's been asked. Regardless of whether the question is added, the keywords counts are updated. If the question is added, keyword mappings are added to the question-keywords table.
        Parameters:
        question - the question to add
        unfilteredSnippets - the number of snippets that were extracted in the process of solving the given question
        Returns:
        true if it was added; false otherwise

      • suggestQuestionsForKeywords

        public Set<String> suggestQuestionsForKeywords(Set<String> keywords)
        Given an arbitrary number of keywords, return a list of partially matching questions ordered by relevance, ties broken by hotness.
        Parameters:
        keywords - the keywords to match against questions
        Returns:
        a sorted map of question Ids to questions, ordered from most relevant to least relevant given the input keywords
